File: A laboratory assistant works on a test sample of a suspected case of the coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - With 116 COVID-19 cases confirmed in South Africa to date, the demand for testing for patients showing signs of the virus will increase. Lancet Laboratories depots/hubs have selected labs which test for coronavirus. Here is a list of the Lancet Labs sites that offer the test:  National List of Covid19 Testing Sites by eNCA.com on Scribd  Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.